OL,3,C'10,000 fewer people to start
OL,4,Capprenticeships this year', says
OL,5,CColleges Wales
OL,7,Fcuts to apprenticeships could cost the
OL,8,FWelsh economy #400 million, according
OL,9,Fto the CEO of Colleges Wales.
OL,11,FColleges and training providers across
OL,12,FWales are facing a cut of around 24%
OL,13,Fto their 2024-25 apprenticeship
OL,14,Fbudgets, compared with the current
OL,15,Facademic year.
OL,17,FSpeaking to ITV Wales' programme,
OL,18,FDavid Hagendyk said: "Our modelling
OL,19,Fsuggests that we are looking at 10,000
OL,20,Ffewer people being able to start
OL,21,Fapprenticeships in September this year.
